  m_Name: 
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: 
  itemName: Item
  collectedMessage: Cats can sleep up to 16 hours a day, adapting a sleep cycle that
    conserves energy for hunting, even in domestic settings. Their ability to fall
    asleep easily and wake up immediately is rooted in survival instincts.
